Hello R-SIG-ECOLOGY members

Enhance your scientific communication by mastering modern tools for presenting complex research findings. AI for Data Visualization and Dashboards led by Hadi Fariborzi (Bissett School of Business, Mount Royal University, Calgary) is now available as an on-demand streaming seminar. This on-demand seminar teaches you how to leverage AI workflows alongside R, Python, and Tableau to build interactive dashboards for complex environmental datasets. Ecologists and environmental scientists can apply these techniques to automate data cleaning and create publication-ready spatial, temporal, and mixed-method visualizations of vegetation or soil patterns. By integrating AI copilots into your workflow, you can accelerate the transition from raw ecological data to reproducible, defensible graphics for peer-reviewed journals and grant proposals.

Access this seminar (https://instats.org/seminar/ai-for-data-visualization-and-dashboards-1) on demand at your own pace, and please pass this to colleagues and students who may find it useful!


Best wishes

